2026-04-21 02:39:10 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control module 1 switch indicator LED circuit', 'Control module 2 switch indicator LED circuit', 'Control module 3 switch indicator LED circuit', 'Control module 4 switch indicator LED circuit', 'Control module 5 switch indicator LED circuit', 'Control module 6 switch indicator LED circuit', 'Control module 7 switch indicator LED circuit', 'Control module 8 switch indicator LED circuit'] hypothesis_explanation="All switch indicator LED circuits in control modules 1–8 are missing both the LED and the series resistor, resulting in open circuit conditions throughout these modules. This breaks the continuity for the main 12V line, preventing current from flowing to the load module and causing the lamp not to turn on. The absence of these components in every control module creates multiple points of interruption in the system's series wiring. The root cause is the removal of the indicator LED and resistor pairs in every control module."
